'''[[Corellian/Legends|Corellian]] leather''' was a material used as upholstery on vehicles such as the [[Lambda-class T-4a shuttle/Legends|''Lambda''-class T-4a shuttle]] and the [[A-1 Deluxe Floater/Legends|A-1 Deluxe Floater]].

==Behind the scenes==
The term may be a reference to "Corinthian leather", a marketing term used to describe the upholstery on certain models of Chrysler luxury cars during the 1970s and 1980s.

